metadata.name: VOODOOZ #278
metadata.description:
Need some luck, happiness, and lucky charm? Alexis Bacci’s VOODOOZ are here for you! Will you dare to mint and to collect?

VOODOOZ is a collection of 512 magical dolls of 3 types: basic, collector and boss - with or without accessories; a tribute to Voodoo culture entirely hand drawn by the comics author Alexis Bacci.

Each VOODOOZ doll has specific and unique magical powers, bringing luck and happiness, a lucky charm in your journey in the NFTs world!

Voodooz come with optional accessories: the SNAKE, the POTION and the RING.

• The SNAKE can complete the inner circle of life and vital energy
• The POTION will help the doll to spell, protect and increase its skills
• The RING gives more power and can be used as a talisman
• The HOLY TRINITY gathers the 3 accessories above

Tip: try to grab a SNAKE + a POTION + a RING and a special VOODOOZ NFT will be airdropped to your wallet for free.

Alexis Bacci is a comics book author who has been working in the cartoon and movie industry for two decades. In 2021 he minted his 1st NFTs on ETH, the Tengu Diaries, and his Girlz series on Tezos.

VOODOOZ are Alexis’ genesis series on fx(hash), pay attention!

metadata.name: Representation #4
metadata.description:
Explore the world of gender politics through vibrant circles.

Representation is an artwork/data visualization about the gender split in parliaments across the world. 

Each minted artwork gets assigned 6 countries from different regions. 1 country from the Pacific, 1 from Europe, 1 from Asia, 1 from the Americas, 1 from Sub-saharan Africa and 1 from the Middle East and North Africa.

Each circle in your artwork represents the gender split of the parliament(s) in one of those countries by using colors. The legend in the bottom right can be used to decipher which color means what.

This artwork was created using p5js.

The artwork adapts to different screen sizes and ratios, so I exploring it on various devices or resizing your browser window. 

Features:

- Circle Size: What size are the circles?
- Circle Distance: How far apart from each other are the circles?
- Circle Scatter: Are the circles scattered on the Y-axis?

twitter: @ada_ada_ada_art

metadata.name: Zaratan #144
metadata.description:
The Generative Token chooses between three primitives (cubes, spheres, triangle stripes) and places it along a parametric curve with parameters varying with noise() function as source of smooth motion.

New shapes are added layer after layer with new forms and colors.

At any time the user can pause the generation by pressing 'p', resume it with 'r' and save a 1600x1600 png with 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- primitives choice (3)
- orientation (0, 90, 180, 270 degrees)
- initial conditions
- shapes evolution
- colors evolution (only 10% will be bi-chromatic)


Press:
- 'p' to pause
- 'r' to resume
- 's' to save a 1600x1600 png image

metadata.name: Habitats #44
metadata.description:
Dive deep into economies & ecologies.

Habitats is an artwork+data visualization about the world economy and the thousands of species, whose existence is threatened by our economies.

Created using p5js.

Remaining supply will be burnt on February 1st.

·Data

Each edition is assigned 3-7 countries as well as a group of species. Each country is represented by a circle, while the species group decides the color scheme.

The GDP (PPP) per capita of each country is shown by the size of the circle. Large circles mean a large GDP, and vice versa.

The amount of threatened species is shown by the density of the circle. A very dense circle means few threatened species, and vice versa.

·Interactivity

Habitats adapts nicely to different screen sizes.

·Save as PNG·

Desktop · S

Mobile · 3 seconds long-press

·Change the shape of data·

·Toggle light mode·

·Toggle background polygon·

metadata.name: Nanopanorama #119
metadata.description:
Distorted noise with weird textures and funky shapes rendered using my rayhatcher algorithm.

4671 characters of pure Javascript, no libraries.

Some options can be changed via the URL:

&lw=.25 : The linewidth in millimetres.
&d=.4 : Line density (multiplier to linewidth).
&h=235 : Page height in millimetres. The aspect ratio is 16:9, for a width of 420mm, suitable for A3 plotting.
&bg=1 : Set to 0 to remove background rectangle (recommended for plotting).

When plotting, it is recommended to use a path reordering / optimizing tool such as axicli or vpype to greatly reduce the plotting time.

metadata.name: TENDER Pass #299
metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Passholders expand their access to unique collaborations with extraordinary artists, indispensable collector tools, curatorial experiences, artwork insights, fine art prints, a thriving community, and more.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.

——

TENDER Pass features unique artwork by punevyr. While all Passes are special, a small number of randomly generated, rarified tokens will come with boosted benefits. If you have a piece with a dark background of any kind, you likely possess one of the following:

Bonus Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Bonus trait get 1 guaranteed reserve spot on all TENDER x Collab projects

Grail Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Grail trait get 2 free mints on all TENDER x Collab projects


New Passholders may access our Discord server that’s linked from our website.
For TENDER Pass benefits and up-to-date details, please visit tender.art/pass


Artwork created with p5.js

---

TENDER x punevyr
July 2022

metadata.name: Phantoms #114
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: Ersbla #253
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: fx(mash) #125
metadata.description:
fx(mash) is my humble contribution to celebrating #fxhashturnsone

This series is based on a simple algorithm - lines of a random length are drawn on a square grid until the grid is full.

I have added a variety of features based on some of my favorite fxhash projects and a few special guests.

This collection is intentionally diverse and disorderly, that's a nice way of saying I only had a short period of time following the release of Acequia. As a result, some of the outputs might be weird, messy, or even bordering on broken (if you get one of the latter please let me know and I'll reimburse you).

Despite being a bit rough around the edges, I hope fx(mash) reflects some measure of my love for the fxhash community. If you're feeling kind, then perhaps it even harks back to the experimental early days :)

The last year has been an incredible journey, thank you for letting me be a part of our story so far.

Controls (in live view):

- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [g] to toggle grain
- Press [h] for a high-res output

Beta Controls (in live view, definitely not fully tested):

- Press [p] to start/pause animation
- Press [i] to slow down animation
- Press [o] to speed up animation

All primary sales go to Savepakistan.


Acknowledgements:

fx(mash) uses Gorilla Sun's grain implementation, a big thanks to him and meezwhite for a great article that is well worth supporting https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain
